<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 17 at 5:10PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A BAND OF GUSTY SNOW SHOWERS WILL AFFECT SOUTHWESTERN
ROANOKE...NORTHEASTERN GILES...SOUTHWESTERN CRAIG... NORTHEASTERN
FLOYD...MONTGOMERY AND SOUTHEASTERN MONROE COUNTIES...
At 506 PM EST, a narrow band of snow showers was located
north of Blacksburg, or over Pembroke, moving southeast at 55 mph.
Winds in excess of 40 mph, a light accumulation of snow, and
reduced visibilities are possible.
Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Christiansburg...
Floyd...
Newport...
Pilot...
Shawsville...
and Sinking Creek.
Those traveling U.S. 460 between Pembroke and Christiansburg and
Shawsville, as well as I-81 between Radford and Salem, should
prepare for poor driving conditions through 530 pm. Be prepared for
snow on roads. Slow down and allow extra time when traveling.</description>
